# From Wikitext

@summary
MediaWiki wikitext is built for collaborative wiki pages, templates, links, and parser extensions. Lessmark is for smaller, fixed-grammar documents without template expansion.

## Headings

Wikitext equals-sign headings become {{code:#}} headings.

@code lang="wikitext"
= Release notes =
== Highlights ==

@code lang="lessmark"
  # Release notes
  ## Highlights

## Links

Internal wiki links become references when the target exists in the same document. External links become safe inline links.

@code lang="wikitext"
[[Install guide]]
[https://lessmark.org Lessmark]

@code lang="lessmark"
{{link:Install guide|docs/getting-started}}
{{link:Lessmark|https://lessmark.org}}

## Lists

Wikitext uses leading punctuation for list depth. Lessmark uses {{code:@list}} and two-space nesting.

@code lang="wikitext"
* one
** nested
* two

@code lang="lessmark"
  @list kind="unordered"
  - one
    - nested
  - two

## Templates

Wikitext templates have no Lessmark equivalent. Render or expand templates before conversion, then write the final content as Lessmark blocks.

@code lang="wikitext"
{{Infobox
| name = Lessmark
}}

@code lang="lessmark"
  @metadata key="name"
  Lessmark

## When to keep Wikitext

Keep wikitext inside MediaWiki, especially when templates, categories, parser functions, or wiki link databases matter. Use Lessmark when documents should be portable source files with no template engine.

## Reference

@link href="https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Help:Wikitext_examples"
MediaWiki wikitext examples
